Designation: Painter of Pain - Surrealist of Self
Bio: Frida Kahlo (1907-1954), Mexican artist known for her self-portraits and works inspired by nature and artifacts of Mexico. Her art explored questions of identity, postcolonialism, gender, class, and race.
